    "---\n",
    "## Step 3 — EDA (3 charts only)\n",
    "\n",
    "EDA = looking at the data before modelling to understand it.\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll do exactly 3 charts:\n",
    "1. Class balance — do we have enough at-risk days?\n",
    "2. Season vs risk — which season triggers what?\n",
    "3. Correlation — which weather features relate to each condition?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a96a5d30",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Chart 1 — Class Balance\n",
    "How many days are at-risk vs safe for each condition?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "0d6940cf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "If at-risk days are much fewer than safe days → class imbalance → need SMOTE\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "targets = ['Migraine', 'Allergy', 'JointPain']\n",
    "colors  = {'Migraine': '#E63946', 'Allergy': '#2A9D8F', 'JointPain': '#E9C46A'}\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, target in zip(axes, targets):\n",
    "    counts = df[target].value_counts().sort_index() #value_counts = frequency check\n",
    "    ax.bar(['No Risk', 'At Risk'],\n",
    "           counts.values,\n",
    "           color=['#A8DADC', colors[target]],\n",
    "           edgecolor='white')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # add count labels on top of bars\n",
    "    for i, v in enumerate(counts.values):\n",
    "        ax.text(i, v + 5, str(v), ha='center', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_title(target, fontweight='bold', color=colors[target])\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('Number of days')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle('How many days are at-risk vs safe? (out of 730 days)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print('If at-risk days are much fewer than safe days → class imbalance → need SMOTE')"
   ]
  },
